This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on morphological tagging, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for this task, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of transfer learning, which is a common approach in neural networks (cs.NE) and the paper also discusses the use of character-level representations, which is a technique used in computer vision (cs.CV) as well as NLP.
